You are about to install PortaBrowseInstall32

You can install this to any harddrive or flashdrive and run it from there, saving ram.
It will remember this drive even if the drive name changes.

After installation you will find "Portable Browser Installer" on the Internet menu.

In older Puppy's you may need to install a newer Yad:

http://distro.ibiblio.org/puppylinux/pet_packages-common32/yad-0.40.3-i686_common32.pet

close this message and you will be given the choice to install this yad.